@flexiarg ukrns/ARGUMENT
@title Argument for the UKRN-S Design Pattern Domain
@keywords service-design, learning-system, network-scale, evidence, bootstrap, UKRN, UKRN-S, ORP, NPT, tetrahedron, ontogenetic
@audience UKRN leadership, Research England, doctoral-training consortia, programme designers, futon developers
@tone analytic-foundational
@style argument
@references [equity/ARGUMENT equity/confident-adaptation equity/protected-interaction equity/shared-maintenance equity/contribution-pathways equity/visible-impact ukrns/open-the-triangle ukrns/diagnose-before-prescribing ukrns/provision-at-network-scale ukrns/measure-where-least-sure ukrns/design-as-function-of-evidence ukrns/distributed-coverage ukrns/computation-as-exploration ukrns/self-application ukrns/worked-contrast ukrns/reader-as-participant ukrns/assumptions-commons ukrns/model-recompute-schedule ukrns/design-state-lineage ukrns/scale-register ukrns/cycle-position-publication ukrns/publication-cadence ukrns/exercise-response-capture ukrns/anchor-case-maintenance ukrns/reader-run-path ukrns/coding-provenance]

@summary A centrally-funded training programme becomes a learning
system when the service that bears it accepts five design disciplines:
deposit evidence at each step, diagnose before prescribing, provision
capabilities at the scale where they pay off, measure where the model
is least sure, and update design as a function of that evidence.  The
five equity patterns (derived from the same ORP case) specify what
must hold *inside* an institution for training to normalise; the five
design patterns specified here specify what must hold *across* the
network for those institutional conditions to become producible rather
than accidental.  The two domains are not parallel sets of
recommendations; the design patterns answer, at service scale, the
structural failures the equity patterns diagnose.

! argument:

  == PART I: What the equity patterns leave unresolved ==

  E1. [Evidence: equity/ARGUMENT, UKRN ORP focus-group transcripts]
  The five equity patterns form a coordination gradient — each
  requires progressively more actors and longer chains to resolve.
  confident-adaptation needs one actor (the central team); visible-impact
  needs a six-plus-actor chain spanning institutions, evaluators, and
  funders.  The gradient explains partial success: institutions that
  resolve the low-coordination patterns still fail at the high-coordination
  ones, producing good delivery and fragile sustainability.

  E2. [Evidence: UKRN-S operational context; role-codebook reanalysis]
  That gradient describes a demand for capabilities individual institutions
  cannot reasonably carry alone.  The role-codebook analysis of the ORP
  transcripts shows the empirical form of the failure: cross-institutional
  evaluation (EV_analyse) was absent across 4/4 transcripts.  No single
  institution was doing it; no institution could be reasonably expected
  to do it; and its absence prevented the programme from learning from
  its own delivery.

  E3. [Evidence: Krowne 2003; evidence-apex derivation in working paper §1]
  A local sustainability triangle (Krowne's participatory, organisational,
  fiscal) sustains what exists locally but is invisible to the network.
  Raising a fourth vertex — shareable evidence — converts isolated
  triangles into connected tetrahedra.  The apex is not an addition to
  the sustainability facets; it is the facet that opens them.

  == PART II: The design-pattern response ==

  The five design patterns specified in this domain are the service-level
  disciplines UKRN-S (or any analogous network service) must adopt to
  supply what the equity gradient requires.  Each pattern is stated as
  a Tension (an axis the service will repeatedly choose on), a set of
  Compositions (2-3 named positions on the axis, not ranked), and a
  Check (engaged-when and failing-when).  Each is summarised below;
  each has its own flexiarg.

  D1. [Pattern: ukrns/open-the-triangle]
  Axis: openness (propagation) ↔ governance cost (ethics, data-handling, exposure).
  Compositions: low-governance loop (Steps 0-2 and 4); governance-first
  (Step 3 upfront); subset pilot (Step 3 with willing institutions).
  Equity joint: answers visible-impact and shared-maintenance at network scale.
  Coordination: Low to very high, depending on the step.

  D2. [Pattern: ukrns/diagnose-before-prescribing]
  Axis: universal service offering ↔ diagnosed service offering.
  Compositions: diagnostic-first (T1 wave as diagnosis); universal bundle
  (accept variance as cost of reach); two-tier (universal baseline +
  diagnostic overlay for multi-constrained profiles).
  Equity joint: answers confident-adaptation at programme level by
  making the scaffold's target explicit per profile.
  Coordination: Low (the service) with Medium input (the institution).

  D3. [Pattern: ukrns/provision-at-network-scale]
  Axis: per-institution contextual fit ↔ network-level scale and comparability.
  Compositions: capability-by-capability (evaluation at network, coordination
  distributed, scaffold between); everything at network scale (with periodic
  local review); convening-only (UKRN-S as convener, capabilities stay local).
  Equity joint: answers protected-interaction, contribution-pathways, and
  visible-impact by placing each capability where it can be sustained.
  Coordination: Medium to Very high.

  D4. [Pattern: ukrns/measure-where-least-sure]
  Axis: value-of-information targeting ↔ stakeholder saliency.
  Compositions: split budget (VoI + saliency allocations run in parallel);
  VoI-only (paper's baseline position, given the learning-system argument);
  saliency-only.
  Equity joint: answers visible-impact at the network scale by making
  measurement a chosen act rather than an audit habit.
  Coordination: Medium (service + institutions selected).

  D5. [Pattern: ukrns/design-as-function-of-evidence]
  Axis: responsiveness (services update with each observation) ↔ stability
  (services resist updates to avoid thrash).
  Compositions: threshold rule (Δ>10pp, smaller shifts as noise); annual
  batching (update once per cycle); continuous update (propagate each
  observation immediately).  The axis is time-active: high responsiveness
  is defensible early, stability becomes more honest as posteriors tighten.
  Equity joint: answers contribution-pathways by making every deposited
  observation a pathway into the design, and closes the loop by making
  visible-impact visible *in the design state itself*.
  Coordination: Very high (the loop is the design).

  D6. [Pattern: ukrns/distributed-coverage]
  Axis: uniform coverage per trainer (every trainer covers all topics) ↔
  distributed coverage across the network (each trainer owns a subset;
  the network guarantees totality).
  Compositions: declared delivery profiles (paper-v2.3 resolution);
  uniform expectation (absorbed-mode signature); curriculum triage per
  institution (honest gaps rather than hidden overload).
  Equity joint: completes the response to protected-interaction that
  provision-at-network-scale answered only partially — network-scale
  coordination support + distributed coverage + declared profiles.
  Coordination: Medium to High (network-scale coverage map maintenance).
  (Added as the sixth main pattern after H5 analysis; see Open Questions.)

  == PART III: The meta-patterns that carry the main patterns ==

  The five main design patterns describe service-level choices.  Four
  further patterns describe how the working paper itself is constructed
  — and, by projection, how UKRN-S could carry out the work the main
  patterns specify.  These are meta-patterns: they are media-theoretic
  (about the paper's construction and why) but they are not only about
  the paper, because the same disciplines project into service practice.

  M1. [Meta-pattern: ukrns/computation-as-exploration]
  Axis: computation-as-exploration (model makes conditional dependencies
  inspectable) ↔ computation-as-prediction (model produces forecasts).
  The paper is at explore-only; UKRN-S could operationalise the same
  stance by re-running the model after each measurement wave.
  Projects into: ukrns/diagnose-before-prescribing, ukrns/measure-where-least-sure,
  ukrns/design-as-function-of-evidence.

  M2. [Meta-pattern: ukrns/self-application]
  Axis: static artefact ↔ instantiating artefact (notebook-as-paper).
  The paper is a notebook that loads evidence, recomputes the model,
  and emits the argument; form instantiates claim.  UKRN-S could
  publish its design state in the same form.
  Projects into: ukrns/design-as-function-of-evidence, ukrns/open-the-triangle.

  M3. [Meta-pattern: ukrns/worked-contrast]
  Axis: abstraction (population-level statements) ↔ concreteness
  (case-level instantiations).  The paper traces FG2A-P1 (delivery-gated)
  and FG3-A (multiply-constrained) as a paired contrast that shows the
  model biting differently.  UKRN-S could maintain anchor cases as
  operational diagnostic instruments.
  Projects into: ukrns/diagnose-before-prescribing.

  M4. [Meta-pattern: ukrns/reader-as-participant]
  Axis: reader-as-consumer (receives conclusions) ↔ reader-as-diagnostic-
  participant (is invited to pick a position).  The paper's Tension /
  Composition / Check form and its Reader exercises teach pattern-reading;
  UKRN-S could address its network in the same posture.
  Projects into: ukrns/diagnose-before-prescribing, ukrns/measure-where-least-sure,
  ukrns/open-the-triangle.

  The meta-patterns are not ornaments on the main patterns; they are the
  disciplines through which the main patterns become legible and
  actionable.  A paper that states the main patterns without the
  meta-patterns — prescriptive conclusions, static artefact, abstract-only,
  consumer-address — would make the weaker version of the same argument,
  and would undercut several of the main patterns by example.

  == PART IV: The implementation patterns that make the stances operational ==

  The meta-patterns describe stances (computation used for exploration,
  artefact instantiates claim, abstract-plus-concrete, reader as
  participant).  Those stances are not self-implementing.  Ten
  implementation patterns specify the operational mechanics through
  which each stance becomes a working discipline — versioning,
  governance of assumptions, recompute schedules, response capture,
  publication cadence, and the rest.

  Implementation patterns differ from main patterns in character.  Main
  patterns describe service-level choices that recur across cycles;
  implementation patterns describe the mechanics that make those
  choices operational.  They use the same Tension / Composition /
  Check structure so the library remains coherent, but their content
  is about plumbing rather than argument.

  I1. [Implementation: ukrns/assumptions-commons]  Governance of
  assumptions-v2.edn.  Serves self-application, computation-as-exploration,
  design-as-function-of-evidence.

  I2. [Implementation: ukrns/model-recompute-schedule]  When the model
  reruns operationally.  Serves self-application, design-as-function-of-evidence,
  measure-where-least-sure.

  I3. [Implementation: ukrns/design-state-lineage]  Versioning of
  service-design changes.  Serves design-as-function-of-evidence's
  traceability invariant.

  I4. [Implementation: ukrns/scale-register]  Publication of capability
  scale choices.  Serves provision-at-network-scale.

  I5. [Implementation: ukrns/cycle-position-publication]  Declaration of
  the current openness/governance Pareto composition.  Serves
  open-the-triangle.

  I6. [Implementation: ukrns/publication-cadence]  Living document vs
  frozen snapshots.  Serves self-application, design-state-lineage.

  I7. [Implementation: ukrns/exercise-response-capture]  What happens
  when readers pick positions.  Serves reader-as-participant.

  I8. [Implementation: ukrns/anchor-case-maintenance]  Stewardship of
  the worked-contrast pair across cycles.  Serves worked-contrast,
  diagnose-before-prescribing.

  I9. [Implementation: ukrns/reader-run-path]  Minimum reproducibility
  infrastructure for rerunners.  Serves self-application, computation-as-exploration.

  I10. [Implementation: ukrns/coding-provenance]  Traceability of the
  qualitative-to-numerical NPT upgrade.  Serves computation-as-exploration,
  diagnose-before-prescribing.

  Without the implementation patterns, the meta-patterns are
  aspirational.  The distinction is not cosmetic: a project that states
  the meta-pattern stances but does not specify the implementation
  mechanics has built a library that describes the argument but does
  not execute it.  The implementation patterns are what lets UKRN-S
  move from a paper about a learning system to a service that behaves
  like one.

  == PART V: Why this is a learning loop, not five recommendations ==

  The five patterns form a cycle: diagnose (D2) → provision (D3) →
  open/deposit (D1) → measure (D4) → update (D5) → re-diagnose with
  updated priors.  The cycle is ontogenetic: each pass deposits
  infrastructure (an instrument, a population model, a scaffold, a
  role codebook, a notebook) that the next pass inherits.  The bootstrap
  sequence in the working paper (Steps 0-4) is one concrete instantiation
  of the cycle starting from the ORP baseline.

  The cycle's closure is what distinguishes a learning system from a
  programme that merely delivers services and collects evaluations.
  In a non-learning system, evidence accrues without reshaping design;
  delivery continues on the same model regardless of what was learned.
  In a learning system, the design state is a function of the evidence
  that has been deposited and the policy chosen for metabolising it.

  == PART VI: What is supplied to the institution, and what is asked ==

  The design patterns describe capabilities the network provides to
  each participating institution:
  - A scaffold that makes expectations inspectable (answers confident-adaptation)
  - Coordination that does not depend on funding-cycle posts (answers protected-interaction)
  - Shared stewardship of materials (answers shared-maintenance)
  - Pathways by which trainers' observations flow back into the design (answers contribution-pathways)
  - Cross-institutional evidence of what the programme is actually producing (answers visible-impact)

  The institution in exchange supplies:
  - A named local actor (not necessarily a funded post) who can carry
    the T1 instrument and the liaison relationship
  - Consent and data-sharing infrastructure for cross-institution evidence
  - Participation in the update cycle: comment on the service's design
    when the posterior shifts, not only when it ossifies

  == PART VII: Relevance to the wider futon stack ==

  The five design patterns generalise beyond training programmes to
  any centrally-coordinated distributed production system that needs
  to learn from its own delivery.  futon7's landscape intelligence
  (knowledge graphs, multi-agent coordination, formal methods) and
  futon3c's mission peripheral both face structurally identical
  service-design questions: what is deposited, what is diagnosed, what
  is provisioned where, what is measured, and how fast the design
  updates.  The UKRN case is domain-specific in vocabulary (NPT, ORP,
  T1, Krowne) but the disciplines are domain-independent.

  == THESIS ==

  The five design patterns specify, in conditional form, what the
  service bearing a distributed training programme must do for the
  programme to become a learning system.  They take the institutional
  failure modes diagnosed by the equity patterns as given and specify
  the service-level responses that convert those failures from
  unresolved constraints into shaped trade-offs.  The working paper
  (UKRN WP) is the first concrete application; the equity and ukrns
  pattern sets together form the argument for UKRN-S's operation as
  a learning system, grounded in observable dynamics rather than
  directive ambition.  UKRN-S is now established as a Community
  Interest Company; the question the patterns engage is not whether
  UKRN-S should exist but what kind of organisation it should be as
  it begins operating.

  == OPEN QUESTIONS ==

  - The bridge between design patterns and equity patterns is
    stated here and in the individual flexiargs; whether the working
    paper's prose should make it equally inspectable is a drafting
    decision for the WP revision.
  - The 'fiscal ↔ mismatch' leg of the Krowne-mode correspondence is
    functional rather than structural; whether the design patterns
    should treat mismatch mode as a distinct customer case (rather
    than a symmetric leg of the mode space) remains a candidate for a
    further design pattern.  (Not addressed by the current set of six.)
  - protected-interaction (breadth-of-topic overload) was originally
    only partially answered by network-scale provisioning.  This gap
    is now addressed by ukrns/distributed-coverage (D6), which treats
    coverage as a network property via declared delivery profiles.
    Resolved.
  - The implementation patterns (I1-I10) are drafted but have not yet
    been operationally tested.  Each will need calibration against
    UKRN-S practice once the service is running; early cycles may
    surface composition choices the current drafts have not anticipated.
  - The empirics underlying assumptions-v2.edn — the qualitative NPT
    coding and its numerical upgrade — need an appendix (proposed as
    Annex C of the working paper) and an implementation pattern
    (ukrns/coding-provenance, now drafted).  The upgrade procedure
    itself has not been formally documented yet.
